Simple video to video - i recommend doing a batch of 16-32 frames to get settings like you want them, then run what you want.

This was made for all the people who wanted to use my sparse control workflow to process 500+ frames or wanted to process all frames, no sparse.  That flow can't handle it due to the masks and control nets and upscales...  Sparse controls work best with sparse controls.  If you want to process everything. This is how you do it.

Creating video to video like this has been available since animate diff and control net came out, Animate diff is excellent with memory and gotten better over time.  

This workflow has no masks, no cutting, no batching/unbatching, no enhancing no frame skipping, It's just a straight-up video changer that changes one video to another.  Because no heavy loading is done, you can process 200+ frames in 1 animate diff batch, really I don't know the limit. I have 12 gb card and processed a 623 frame video with this.. at once.  It took FOREVER... but it worked... Wasn't perfect because settings were not good for the video.  Do a batch of 16 to test settings before going with whatever you're trying.

2 Choices of controls - bypass what you dont use, any controls used here will increase memory used.  But not by too much if they are smaller models.  fp16  
lineart (your choice)
depth map
Really, you could probably load any... haven't tested, but I'm sure open pose or others work too.  I'm not your dad, have fun.

Can use ip adaptor, but it does increase memory needed and can muck up some videos depending on what model ipadaptor you use and what weight, this can also insert a reference for backgrounds/colors

This is all you need for 80% of videos. Some work with just lineart, some just depth, some combo.

I have made this compatible with my sparse control up scalers via a loading module in the sparse video workflow.  You can do the video here, and then load it into the sparse controls workflow to upscale and enhance if you want.

Ksampler 1  0 - 8 steps LCM sgm uniform  end at min 4 max 12  

Ksampler 2  4- 8 steps LCM sgm uniform  min 2 max 12  Going too high here or too low will lose your movement

Can skip lcm if you want, I like it because I am impatient, and I test a lot of things.

Size is your choice depending on your memory, can crop and upscale/downscale initial video its size is the video's start size, I do max 512x512 first step with 1.5 or 2x upscale.

Some good settings - different line arts work Line art realistic copies closely, hed is softer etc

Good change, decent movement copy
Depth start 0 end 1, scaled weights .825
hed start .2-.4 end .8 scaled weights .825

Good movement, little change
realistic Line art start 0 end 1, weights, .9
depth start 0 end 1, weights 0.825

Either one can work alone on some videos.  Depth offers more change, line offers better movement, and body parts.
If you want to change background, depth is the best option, with something like HED with start and stops in the middle.

It's much easier to change the person than the background unless using low weights on lineart and higher weights on GOOD depth maps.
1.5 - 2 upscale is good here. 2 is best, could go higher if you want/can

Frames uses the frames as image to image. 
can change the steps from 0 to something else in this case, I don't use this as it does not allow enough change for me even less than lineart, but it's an option if you want.

Empty creates a new video without the images only the control nets, allows more change but can be more unstable, I use this mostly.

Main prompts, only prompts, change the video here, clothing in (clothing and color:1.2), describe all clothing, and negative out things like jewelry, lace, bracelets, or anything else you don't want showing up in a random frame.  if you want these things, describe them like clothing.

embeddings work here quite well and prefer them to lora due to more directed changes.  Lora for one thing can affect other things much more.

I rarely use this control net, but when using more steps than default it can lose fine movement. 

You can use this and end it .4 - .8 if you are loosing certain motions from the first step, more you use here harder it is to fix anything
